gory:Chicago Blackhawks players]]\n[[Category:HC Dinamo Minsk players]]\n[[Category:HC Dynamo Moscow players]]\n[[Category:EHC Freiburg players]]\n[[Category:HC Fribourg-Gott\u00e9ron players]]\n[[Category:HK Gomel players]]\n[[Category:HPK players]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey players at the 1998 Winter Olympics]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey players at the 2002 Winter Olympics]]\n[[Category:Indianapolis Ice players]]\n[[Category:Kalamazoo Wings (1974\u20132000) players]]\n[[Category:HC Khimik Voskresensk players]]\n[[Category:Krefeld Pinguine players]]\n[[Category:HK Neman Grodno players]]\n[[Category:Olympic ice hockey players of Belarus]]\n[[Category:Revier L\u00f6wen players]]\n[[Category:Soviet ice hockey players]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Minsk]]\n[[Category:Tivali Minsk players]]\n[[Category:Belarusian expatriates in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox ice hockey player \n| played_for = [[HC Dinamo Minsk|Dinamo Minsk]]<br>[[HC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]]<br>[[HC Fribourg-Gott\u00e9ron]]<br>[[Chicago Blackhawks]]<br>[[HPK]]<br>[[HC Bolzano]]<br>[[Krefeld Pinguine]]<br>[[Revierl\u00f6wen Oberhausen]]\n| ntl_team = Belarus\n| position = [[Winger (ice hockey)|Right Wing]]\n| shoots = Right\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 5\n| weight_lb = 212\n| image =  \n| image_size = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1968|8|10|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Minsk]], [[Byelorussian Soviet Socialist Republic|Byelorussian SSR]], [[Soviet Union|URS]]\n| draft = 220th overall\n| draft_year = 1991\n| draft_team = [[Chicago Blackhawks]]\n| career_start = 1984\n| career_end = 2005\n}}\n'''Alexander Leonidovich Andrijevsky''' ({{lang-ru|\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u0301\u043d\u0434\u0440 \u041b\u0435\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0301\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0301\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439}}; born August 10, 1968) is a [[Belarus]]ian retired professional [[ice hockey]] player who played one game in the [[National Hockey League]] for the [[Chicago Blackhawks]]. He is currently the head coach for [[HC Sibir Novosibirsk]] of the [[Kontinental Hockey League]] (KHL).\n\n==Playing career==\nAndrijevsky spent the first six seasons of his career with his hometown team [[HC Dinamo Minsk|Dinamo Minsk]] between 1984 and 1990. In 1991, he moved to [[HC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]]. 1991 was also the year Andrijevski was drafted by the Chicago Blackhawks, who selected him 220th overall in the [[1991 NHL Entry Draft|10th round]]. After one more season with Dynamo, Andrijevsky moved to [[North America]], signing with the Blackhawks. For the 1992-93 season, he was assigned to the [[Indianapolis Ice]] of the [[International Hockey League (1945-2001)|International Hockey League]] before being called up by the Blackhawks for his [[List of players who played only one game in the NHL|only NHL game]].\n\nThe next season, Andrijevsky played just four games for Indianapolis before moving to the [[Kalamazoo Wings]] in the same league. It would be his final year in North America as he moved to the [[Liiga|SM-liiga]] in [[Finland]], joining [[HPK]] where he spent four seasons. He then split the 1998-99 season playing in [[Italian Hockey League - Serie A]] in [[Italy]] for [[HC Bozen\u2013Bolzano|HC Bolzano]] and in the [[Deutsche Eishockey Liga]] in [[Germany]] for the [[Krefeld Pinguine]]. Following a spell in the [[2nd Bundesliga (ice hockey)|2nd Bundesliga]] for [[EHC Neuwied]], He returned to the DEL with [[Revierl\u00f6wen Oberhausen]] for two seasons.\n\nAndrijevsky returned to Russia in 2001 with [[Atlant Moscow Oblast|Khimik Voskresensk]] of the [[Supreme Hockey League|Vysshaya Hokkeinaya Liga]], the country's second-tier league. He later returned to the 2nd Bundesliga with [[EHC Freiburg]] before returning to Belarus with [[HK Gomel]] and a return to Dinamo Minsk to finish his career.\n\n==International career==\nAndrijevsky was a member of the [[Belarus men's national ice hockey team|Belarus national team]] and played with the team in the [[1998 Winter Olympics|1998]] and [[2002 Winter Olympics|2002]] [[Winter Olympics]]. He also represented the team in four [[Ice Hockey World Championships]].\n\n==Career statistics==\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"text-align:center; width:60em\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! colspan=\"3\"  bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" |  \n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" |  \n! colspan=\"5\"                    | [[Regular season]]\n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" |  \n! colspan=\"5\"                    | [[Playoffs]]\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! [[Season (sports)|Season]]\n! Team\n! League\n! GP\n! [[Goal (ice hockey)|G]]\n! [[Assist (ice hockey)|A]]\n! [[Point (ice hockey)|Pts]]\n! [[Penalty (ice hockey)|PIM]]\n! GP\n! G\n! A\n! Pts\n! PIM\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1984\u201385||[[HC Dinamo Minsk|Dinamo Minsk]]||Soviet-2||3||0||0||0||0||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1985\u201386||Dinamo Minsk||Soviet-2||11||3||4||7||4||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1986\u201387||Dinamo Minsk||Soviet-2||38||3||5||8||39||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1987\u201388||Dinamo Minsk||Soviet-2||50||2||5||7||20||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1988\u201389||Dinamo Minsk||[[Soviet Championship League|Soviet]]||7||1||1||2||2||*25||9||7||16||6\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1989\u201390||Dinamo Minsk||Soviet||47||16||12||28||32||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1990\u201391||[[HC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]]||Soviet||44||9||8||17||28||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1991\u201392||Dynamo Moscow||Soviet||31||9||8||17||14||7||2||1||3||8\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1991\u201392||Dynamo Moscow-2||Soviet-3||3||5||1||6||0||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| [[1991\u201392 Nationalliga A season|1991\u201392]] ||[[HC Fribourg-Gott\u00e9ron|Fribourg-Gott\u00e9ron]]||[[National League A|NLA]]||1||0||0||0||0||||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1992\u201393||[[Tivali Minsk]]||[[Belarusian Hockey League|BHL]]||11||5||2||7||14||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1992\u201393||[[Chicago Blackhawks]]||[[National Hockey League|NHL]]||1||0||0||0||0||--||--||--||--||--\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1992\u201393||[[Indianapolis Ice]]||[[International Hockey League (1945-2001)|IHL]]||66||26||25||51||59||4||2||3||5||10\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1993\u201394||Indianapolis Ice||IHL||4||0||1||1||2||--||--||--||--||--\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1993\u201394||[[Kalamazoo Wings]]||IHL||57||6||22||28||58||1||0||0||0||2\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1994\u201395||Tivali Minsk||[[International Hockey League (1992\u201396)|IHL]]||4||1||1||2||4||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1994\u201395||Tivali Minsk||BHL||10||11||7||18||20||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1994\u201395||[[HPK]]||[[Liiga|SM-l]]||17||8||9||17||18||--||--||--||--||--\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1995\u201396||HPK||SM-l||43||18||15||33||75||9||7||1||8||4\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1996\u201397||HPK||SM-l||42||17||28||45||26||10||2||4||6||2\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1997\u201398||HPK||SM-l||25||7||9||16||22||--||--||--||--||--\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" \n| 1998\u201399||[[Hockey Club Bolzano-Bozen|Bolzano]]||[[Italian Hockey League - Serie A|ITA]]||2||0||0||0||4||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1998\u201399||Bolzano||[[Alpenliga]]||35||23||14||37||16||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1998\u201399||[[Krefeld Pinguine]]||[[Deutsche Eishockey Liga|DEL]]||13||5||4||9||8||4||0||1||1||6\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 1999\u20132000||[[Revierl\u00f6wen Oberhausen]]||DEL||31||13||18||31||40||*12||3||10||13||4\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1999\u20132000||[[EHC Neuwied]]||[[2nd Bundesliga (ice hockey)|2.GBun]]||17||10||10||20||12||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 2000\u201301||Revierl\u00f6wen Oberhausen||DEL||56||11||13||24||28||3||0||0||0||0\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 2001\u201302||[[Atlant Moscow Oblast|Khimik Voskresensk]]||Rus-2||35||7||18||25||22||14||7||7||14||8\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 2002\u201303||Khimik Voskresensk||[[Supreme Hockey League|Rus-2]]||16||2||5||7||34||||||||||\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 2002\u201303||[[EHC Freiburg]]||2.GBun||15||9||4||13||4||11||2||1||3||31\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 2003\u201304||[[HK Gomel]]||BHL||32||14||14||28||16||9||3||1||4||0\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 2004\u201305||Dinamo Minsk||BHL||40||8||15||23||46||||||||||\n|}\n* *Relegation\n\n==External links==\n*{{icehockeystats}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Andrievsky, Alexander}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belarusian ice hockey coaches]]\n[[Category:Belarusian ice hockey right wingers]]\n[[Category:Bolzano HC players]]\n[[Category:Chicago Blackhawks draft picks]]\n[[Category:Chicago Blackhawks players]]\n[[Category:HC Dinamo Minsk players]]\n[[Category:HC Dynamo Moscow players]]\n[[Category:EHC Freiburg players]]\n[[Category:HC Fribourg-Gott\u00e9ron players]]\n[[Category:HK Gomel players]]\n[[Category:HPK players]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey players at the 1998 Winter Olympics]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey players at the 2002 Winter Olympics]]\n[[Category:Indianapolis Ice players]]\n[[Category:Kalamazoo Wings (1974\u20132000) players]]\n[[Category:HC Khimik Voskresensk players]]\n[[Category:Krefeld Pinguine players]]\n[[Category:HK Neman Grodno players]]\n[[Category:Olympic ice hockey players of Belarus]]\n[[Category:Revier L\u00f6wen players]]\n[[Category:Soviet ice hockey players]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Minsk]]\n[[Category:Tivali Minsk players]]\n[[Category:Belarusian expatriates in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "DaRabidMonkey", "label": "safe", "comment": "Update team coached", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Andrievsky"}
